Betty Friedan, a pioneer of the feminist movement, founded NOW and advocated for the Equal Rights Amendment.
Her book ignited modern feminism, challenging societal norms.
Friedan's impact on women's rights was immense, though she later shifted focus to ageism.
Despite criticism, her work reshaped American culture.
Friedan's legacy lives on through activists like Eleanor Smeal and Kim Gandy.
The ongoing debate on motherhood reflects changing societal expectations.
